# tree.conf — selective reveal by ternary tree path
#
# Only applies when HASH_TREE=ternary and TREE_CONF=tree.conf in site.conf.
#
# Each line maps a tree path prefix to reveal or lock.
# Files hash deterministically to paths like 0/1/2/0/filename.html.
# Use locksite.py encrypt to generate tree.txt (admin sitemap) showing
# which files map to which paths.
#
# Format: <path_prefix>  reveal|lock
# Wildcards: 0/* means everything under node 0 at that level.
# More specific rules override less specific ones.
#
# Examples:
#   0/*       reveal    # everything under node 0 is public
#   1/0/*     reveal    # this specific branch too
#   1/1/*     lock      # explicitly locked (default)
#   2/*       lock      # everything under node 2 locked
